item.dc:creator: @xeez xeez`
item.description:
@xeez wrote:

[quote=“Frostie21, post:27, topic:293868”][quote author=xEnt link=topic=388795.msg2907007#msg2907007 date=1249859597]
prison break, dexter, heroes, lost[br][br][size=1]Posted on: August 09, 2009, 05:13:44 pm[/size][hr]if your into anime, bleach & Naruto shippuden
[/quote]

Perfect list imo,even though I don’t watch lost/pb much.[/quote]Neither do I. Both of them started out great, but have made most watchers lose interest in them due to the need to continue these series (even though Prison Break is already over). Lost is extending it too much. They have already converted it from a series with suspense and supernatural things to a sci-fi.

Prison Break’s first three seasons were excellent. But coming to the fourth season, changed most of the characters’ personalities. For example, “T-Bag”, who was convicted for being a pedophile and a mass-murderer, never showed guilt of any kind when killing someone; and wouldn’t think twice before doing so. In one of the episodes in the 4th season, you see how he pities a “priest”, and negates to kill him; which leads to him (T-Bag) being kidnapped.

Belleck, who was a dirty cop throughout the cons’ sentence in jail, and would basically kill for a few extra cents, actually sacrificed himself (and died) to save the cons who had escaped from the prison he had guarded, and who he had almost killed for $5 million dollars.

I would back-up my hatred against Lost, but I haven’t seen an episode since the 3rd (or 4th) season.
